      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Thou shalt become an astonishment, a proverb, and a by-word — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "“And do we not hear and see this prophecy fulfilled almost every day? Is not the avarice, usury, and hard-heartedness of a Jew grown proverbial? And are not their persons generally odious among all sorts of people? Mohammedans, heathens, and Christians, however they may disagree in other points, yet generally agree in vilifying, abusing, and persecuting the Jews. In most places where they are tolerated, they are obliged to live in a separate quarter by themselves, (as they did in London in the Old Jewry,) and to wear some badge of distinction. Their very countenances commonly distinguish them from the rest of mankind. They are in all respects treated as if they were of another species.” ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "— ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Bishop Newton.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
